<br>
 Proc rates are skewed based on weapon delay. So that over time a slower weapon and a faster weapon will get the same number of procs on average. Slow weapons on average proc on more swings. So say you get 100 swings with weapon A in 60 seconds, and only 50 with weapon B. To get proc rate on A would be 50% of proc rate on B. So say A procs every 10 swings, to get you 10 procs in 60 seconds, weapon B with double the delay will proc on average every 5 swings to get 10 procs in 60 seconds.<br>
<br>
 Problem with this system as I understand it is with haste on slower weapons end up proccing considerably more than speedy weapons. Since it works based on base delay and not hasted. The actual delay of slower weapons gets lowered more by haste spells than on faster weapons, and they in turn proc more.<br>
<br>
